      <h2>When an electrical issue needs urgent help</h2>
      <p>Some electrical jobs can be scheduled. Others need fast attention because they can create shock, fire, or equipment damage risk. Call immediately if you notice sparks, smoke, a burning smell, a breaker that will not reset, partial power loss, buzzing from the panel, damaged wiring, or water near an outlet, switch, appliance, or panel.</p>
      <p>If it is safe, stop using the affected device and turn off the related breaker. Do not touch wet electrical equipment, exposed wiring, or a panel that smells hot. A quick photo or short description can help explain the issue, but safety comes first.</p>
    </div>
